    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single below-threshold factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 1 vs. required Gradation 2) reflects the use of a single ASTM F1717 load configuration. This gap is mitigated by the strong quantitative output comparison results (all E/uval < 1.96, all percent differences < 10%) and by the two-laboratory experimental dataset. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level decision for this Class II device submission.",
